Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 13
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 13

Chronology Exhibit — Your Case in One Page

⚖️ Core Message

A neutral, dated timeline lets any reader verify what happened, fast.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Columns: Date, Event, Source (Exhibit/Docket), Effect/Prejudice.
2. Keep entries factual and short; link each to proof.
3. Cite the timeline in every motion requesting relief.
4. Update after each filing; export to PDF and attach as Exhibit 1.
📝 Assignment

Build a 12‑line timeline (Date/Event/Source/Effect) for your case; attach as Exhibit 1.
✅ Model Response

EXHIBIT 1 — TIMELINE (excerpt)

Date        Event                         Source            Effect

2025‑07‑21  TRO filed                     Dkt 12            Relief sought

2025‑07‑31  USPS delivered to Clerk       Ex. A             Delay begins

2025‑08‑02  Clerk docketed (late)         Dkt 18            Apparent untimely

 

💡 Reflection Summary

One page of dates can beat ten pages of rhetoric.
🎨 Visual Concept

A horizontal timeline with pins labeled by exhibits.
